#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/special_effects/halo.rst:124
msgid "Lens Flares"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/special_effects/halo.rst:126
msgid ""
"Our eyes have been trained to believe that an image is real if it shows "
"artifacts that result from the mechanical process of photography. *Motion"
" blur*, *Depth of Field*, and *lens flares* are just three examples of "
"these artifacts. The first two are discussed in the *chapter rendering*; "
"the latter can be produced with special halos. A simulated lens flare "
"tells the viewer that the image was created with a camera, which makes "
"the viewer think that it is authentic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/special_effects/halo.rst:135
msgid ""
"We create lens flares in Blender from a mesh object using first the "
"*Halo* button and then the *Flare* options in the *Shaders* Panel of the "
"material settings. Try turning on *Rings* and *Lines*, but keep the "
"colors for these settings fairly subtle. Play with the *Flares:* number "
"and *Fl. seed:* settings until you arrive at something that is pleasing "
"to the eye. You might need to play with *Boost:* for a stronger effect "
"Fig. :ref:`fig-bi-material-halo-flare` settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/special_effects/halo.rst:144
msgid ""
"Note that this tool does not simulate the physics of photons traveling "
"through a glass lens; it's just an eye candy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/special_effects/halo.rst:148
msgid ""
"Blender's lens flare looks nice in motion, and disappears when another "
"object occludes the flare mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/special_effects/halo.rst:156
msgid "Lens Flare."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/special_effects/halo.rst:160
msgid "Halo Texturing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/special_effects/halo.rst:162
msgid ""
"By default, textures are applied to objects with Object coordinates and "
"reflects on the halos by affecting their color, as a whole, on the basis "
"of the color of the vertex originating the halo. To have the texture take"
" effect *within* the halo, and hence to have it with varying colors or "
"transparencies press the *Texture* button; this will map the whole "
"texture to *every* halo. This technique proves very useful when you want "
"to create a realistic rain effect using particle systems, or similar."
msgstr ""

